------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components (permissive, redistributed as part of the build):
  - thiserror (MIT OR Apache-2.0)           — align-core error types
  - proptest  (MIT OR Apache-2.0, dev only) — property tests
  - Tauri v2 and ecosystem (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — desktop shell
  - React (MIT), Vite (MIT)                 — frontend

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled (compiled-in) alignment engine:
  - KAlign v3.5.1 (Apache-2.0) — Timo Lassmann, https://github.com/TimoLassmann/kalign
    Vendored as a git submodule at crates/align-extern/vendor/kalign and compiled
    into the application in-process via the `align-extern` crate's `kalign` feature
    (the higher-quality "KAlign" option in Align → Engine). Its full Apache-2.0
    license text is retained at crates/align-extern/vendor/kalign/COPYING.
    The default build does NOT include it (feature off ⇒ pure-Rust, no submodule).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GPL alignment tools (MUSCLE v5, Clustal Omega) are NOT bundled or linked. If
ever integrated they would only be detected and invoked as separate,
user-installed processes — keeping Iberalign's own code under a non-GPL license.
Phylogenetic tree tools (FastTree/IQ-TREE) likewise remain separate processes.
See iberprime-spec.md §11.
